    {
      "id": "bc9950c3ae84be1f577d9385b8eb11c446a7a6f4",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 655,
        "name": "Arshad Hussain",
        "email": "arshad.hussain@aeoncomputing.com",
        "username": "arshad512"
      },
      "date": "2024-02-21 00:15:22.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\nThanks for bringing these scripts in!\n\nThis is good as is. Mabybe couple of improvements for next version.\n\nI would really like to have errors=nn/warnings=nn instead of cumulative number. The reason is that soon we should be near zero errors, however warnings would still be left. Warnings mostly is over 80 chars..., string which is split accross two lines and multi line comment not ending on new line and few others. Unfortunately, these warnings would still remain, specially \"over 80 chars\" as these are errors/messages which are printed and no way to change them. Having errors/warnings numbers would give correct snapshot. \n\nSecond, git-checkpatch have it also take a folder as an input?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "a8fa281e9ee9d4ee9e35b2daac7ff462acb3c87f",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 931,
        "name": "Timothy Day",
        "email": "timday@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "timday"
      },
      "date": "2024-02-21 18:24:08.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nThanks for the review.\n\nSplitting up errors and warnings seems like a good idea. I'll have to give that a try.\n\ngit-checkpatch should work with folders. I think you have to do something like 'git checkpatch lustre/*'. It takes a long time to run (usually), so you might have to wait a bit before anything comes up.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
